# intution:-
These are ***the 3 conditions which must not follow to if we want to send a friend request according to the question.***
```
age[y] <= 0.5 * age[x] + 7
age[y] > age[x]
age[y] > 100 && age[x] < 100
```

Think of something, yes take all the cases diffently what must not occur
  after thinking you know we need to do sorting because:-
  1. age[y] <= age[x]  so to do so  do sorting 
  2.     age[y] > 100 than we must find age[x] >= 100  **** hint no.2****
  3.     age[x] must be =>     age[x] < 2*(age[y]-7)   so to find this index we need to apply lower_bound function **(so do sorting** 

---------age[y]-------------------------age[x]-------- -----    sorted array
            index = i                                  index = j

so all the element which follow age[y] <= age[x]  it will be    j-i-1

Let's talk about why we need map here
so take example no.1 =>     *[16,16]*     each of them can send friend request to each other. but we have sorted the array so we need their first occurence that's why we are using map.

**second condition will be automatically followed no need to worrrrrry because of sorting**

**Here is the code:-**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int numFriendRequests(vector<int>& ages) {
        int ans = 0;
        sort(ages.begin(), ages.end());


        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        for(int i = 0; i < ages.size(); i++) {
            if(!mp.count(ages[i])) mp[ages[i]] = i;
        }


        for(int i = 0; i < ages.size(); i++) {
            int x= lower_bound(ages.begin(), ages.end(), 2*(ages[i]-7)) - ages.begin();
            if(x <= i) continue;
            ans += x-mp[ages[i]]-1; 
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

