This question comes from Facebook tech screening: https://leetcode.com/discuss/interview-question/469422/facebook-phone-count-all-friend-requests

But note that in there it says 
> A centaur over 100 years old will not send a friend request to a recipient under 100 years old. But centaurs under 100 years old can friend each other.

whereas in Leetcode, it says
> "A Person x will not send a friend request to a person y if age[y] > 100 && age[x] < 100". 

Which is the opposite. So much so, that Leetcode also says that: 
> "A Person x will not send a friend request to a person y if age[y] > age[x]"

which is a generalization of the previous one. This makes this solution pass:

```
    public int numFriendRequests(int[] ages) {
        Arrays.sort(ages);
