I first have some difficulty to understand the problem.
The three condition is C1, C2 and C3
A not friend request B: C1||C2||C3
A friend request B: !(C1||C2||C3)=!C1&&!C2&&!C3
!C1: B>0.5A+7. If B=A, B>14
!C2: B<=A
!C3: B<=100 || A>=100, this always is true
We build a hash map (using a vector is simpler) and check the !C1 and !C2.
same age friend request if met condition: N*(N-1)
different age friend request if met condition: N*M

