# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
I think the problem was somewhat poorly phrased since condition 2 is essentially condition 3, where you don't friend people older than you. With that in mind, we can sort the array first and essentially eliminate needing to check 2/3 of conditions (since anyone before you in age won't friend you back).

After that it's just a matter of checking for the calculated age condition, with a small statement to handle when people are the same age.

# Complexity
