# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

find all the age less then age[i] and find minimum age[j] (j<i) such that it follows the condition of friend request and all the ages after jth age till age[i] will follow the condition to send request.
so add (i-j) to count.

Along with the upper approach here is one catch.

if we have same elements like [16,16,16]
now as per the above example all the three 16 will be able to make friends with other two 16 so total requests sent is 3*(2 each)=6
so in such repeating ages what we will do is to count the number of repeating ages and find the requests for last most repeated age and multiply that answer with total number of repeated ages....

# Approach
