# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Count amount of people for each age. Go through hash array and check conditions for `x` and `y`. Get amount of requests by multiplying `arr[x]` and `arr[y]`. If `x` equals `y` we subtract `1` as a person will not send a friend request to themself.

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number[]} ages
 * @return {number}
 */
var numFriendRequests = function(ages) {
    let arr = new Array(121).fill(0);
    let result = 0;

    for (let i = 0; i < ages.length; i++) {
        arr[ages[i]]++;
    }

    for (let x = 0; x < arr.length; x++) {
        for (let y = 0; y <= x; y++) {
            if (y <= (0.5 * x + 7)) {
                continue;
            } else {
                if (x === y) {
                    result += (arr[x] - 1) * arr[y];
                } else {
