# Intuition
Make a prefix array to store the count of people till the age (age == index).
To make prefix array first we will make a hashmap to store count of people of particular age (without sorting);

# Approach
- Make a **count** array to store the count of people of particular age.
- Make a **prefixSum** array to store the count of people less than or equal to the current age (index).
- Traverse the **prefixSum** array and add the number of people satisfy the condition given in question in contant time.
- Please **upvote** if you find approach helpful.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numFriendRequests(vector<int>& ages) {
        vector<int> count(121, 0);

        for(auto it: ages) {
            count[it]++;
        }

        vector<int> prefixSum(121, 0);
        for(int i=1; i<121; i++) {
            prefixSum[i] = prefixSum[i-1] + count[i];
        }

        int res = 0;
        for(int i=1; i<121; i++) {
            int min = (i/2) + 7;
            if(min >= i) {
                continue;
            }

            res += (count[i] * (count[i] - 1));
            res += (prefixSum[i-1] - prefixSum[min]) * count[i];
        }

        return res;
    }
};
```

