# Intuition/Approach
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Firstly I looked at the lowest number that can send/recieve friend requests. This turns out to be 15 as 15*0.5+7=14.5, which is lower than 15. Additionally 15 is not larger than 15.

With every other n (1<=n<=14) this won't work. 
I.e. 14*0.5+7 =14 which is equal to 14 and therefore wont work according to the first rule (age[y] <= 0.5 * age[x] + 7 =>will not send a friend request );

After this one can add up every number with equal value in a seperate int[] Array with the length of 121 as 1<=n<=120. 

Next one can add up every possible friend Request between certain ages. 
Within the same age>=15 every person of that age can send every other person of the same age a friend request. 
friendRequests+=(sameNumbers-1)*sameNumbers; 
Here numbers are the individual ages.

Every person of a certain age can send friend requests to people of lower ages who are equal to age/2+7+1.
The total amount of people of lower ages which a specific age can send friend requests to are summed up in a loop.
Finally the total amount of people of a certain age send friend requests to people of lower ages up to the lower bound (age/2+7+1).

friendRequests+=validLowerNumbers*sameNumbers;

Finally this can be done for every age individually and summed up and returned.






# Code
```
class Solution {
    int friendRequests=0;
    int[] totalCount= new int[121];

    public int numFriendRequests(int[] ages) {

        for(int a=0;a<ages.length;a++)
        {
            totalCount[ages[a]]+=1;
        }

        int sameNumbers;
        int validLowerNumbers=0;

        for(int a=15; a<121;a++)
        {
            int lowestAccepted= a/2+7+1;
            sameNumbers=totalCount[a];

            validLowerNumbers=0;

            for(int b=lowestAccepted; b<a;b++)
            {
                validLowerNumbers+=totalCount[b];
            }
            friendRequests+=(sameNumbers-1)*sameNumbers;
            friendRequests+=validLowerNumbers*sameNumbers;
        }

        return friendRequests;   
    }
}
```

