Essentially, we need to find the longest array with a sum of - (sum(array) - x). If we do find this, this might either be - 
1. Starting from the left end: In this case, We will have found the answer which has minimum length from right
2. Somewhere in the middle: Will be a valid answer since we can pick elements from either sides
3. Starting from right end: Similar to 1

We find such a longest array and the answer will be length(array) - length of longest array as found earlier

Code in Java - 
