Just convert to another question:
The longest subarray with sum =  (sum of nums - x);

Then the question is much easier. Just play the trick of calculating presum and store in map. 
For this type of question, please refer to leetcode 560:
https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/

```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) sum += num;
        int target = sum - x;

        // find the longest subarray that sums = target
        int presum = 0;
        int res = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0, -1); // For the special case presum == target

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            presum += nums[i];
            if (!map.containsKey(presum)) map.put(presum, i); // Always store smallest index
            if (map.containsKey(presum - target)) {
                res = Math.max(res, i - map.get(presum - target));
            }
        }

        if (res == Integer.MIN_VALUE) return -1;
        return nums.length - res;
    }
}
```

