# Approach
Sliding Window Technique

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
            sum += nums[i];
        sum -= x;
        if (sum == 0)
            return n;
        int start = 0, curSum = 0, len = 0;
        for (int end = 0; end < n; end++) {
            curSum += nums[end];
            while (start < n && curSum > sum) {
                curSum -= nums[start];
                start++;
            }
            if (curSum == sum)
                len = max (len, end - start + 1);
        }   
        if (!len) 
            return -1;
        return n - len;     
    }
};
```

