solutions.content:
To solve this problem first we need to calculate the maximum length of subarray with sum which is equal to difference of total sum and x. 

**Example:**
**nums** = [3,2,5,4,11,5]
**x** = 10

Total sum = 3 + 2 + 5 + 4 + 11 + 5 = 30
Sum - x = 20

Length of maximum subarray with sum = 20 is 3 as shown;
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/cc41dccc-38e7-41bf-a129-e3909f1574d2_1654924475.3698084.png)


Clearly we can say that the sum of remaining elements other than subarray is x. So we need to return the remaining length other than subarray.

That is we need to return 6 - 3 which is equal to 3.
So the **output** for the above test case is 3.

**C++ code**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        int l = 0;
        int sum = 0, res = 0, maxi = -1,n = nums.size();
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++) // To calculate total sum
        {
            sum = sum + nums[i];
        }
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++) // To calculate length of maximum subarray with 'sum = total sum - x'
        {
            res = res + nums[i];
            while((l<n) && (sum - x < res))
            {
                res = res - nums[l];
                l++;
            }
            if(sum - res == x)
            {
                maxi = max(i - l + 1, maxi);
            }
        }
        if(maxi == -1)
        {
            return -1;
        }
        return n - maxi;

    }
};
```

**Time complexity -** O(N)
**Space complexity -** O(1)

