solutions.content:
Finding the minimum number of removing is equal to finding the maximum number of remaining.
Sliding window can help us find the maximum number of remaining easily!
```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.length;

        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) 
            sum += nums[i];
        int target = sum - x;

        if (target < 0)
            return -1;
        if (target == 0)
            return n;

        int left = 0, right = 0;
        int maximum = 0;
        while (right < n) {
            target -= nums[right++];

            while (target < 0)
                target += nums[left++];

            if (target == 0)
                maximum = Math.max(maximum, right - left);
        }

        return maximum == 0 ? -1 : nums.length - maximum;
    }
}
```

However, when I first meet this question, I come up with a solution which use greedy and backtrack.
When remove the number (assume you have [a, ..., b]), choose the bigger one (assume a is bigger than b, so we choose a), if it doesn't work, backtrack, choose the other one (b).
I think it's a nice idea but it meets TLE, I also post this code below
```
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        LinkedList<Integer> removed = new LinkedList<>();
        return helper(nums, 0, nums.length - 1, x, removed) ? removed.size() : -1;
    }

    private boolean helper(int[] nums, int left, int right, int x, LinkedList<Integer> removed) {
        if (x == 0)
            return true;

        if (x < 0)
            return false;

        if (left > right)
            return false;

        if (nums[left] > x && nums[right] > x)
            return false;

        if (nums[left] >= nums[right]) { // greedy
            removed.add(nums[left]);
            if (helper(nums, left + 1, right, x - nums[left], removed))
                return true;
            removed.removeLast(); // backtrack

            removed.add(nums[right]);
            if (helper(nums, left, right - 1, x - nums[right], removed))
                return true;
            removed.removeLast();
        } else {
            removed.add(nums[right]);
            if (helper(nums, left, right - 1, x - nums[right], removed))
                return true;
            removed.removeLast();

            removed.add(nums[left]);
            if (helper(nums, left + 1, right, x - nums[left], removed))
                return true;
            removed.removeLast();
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

