The idea here is to find **maximun length continuous subarray** which can give sum equals to **Target**.  Here, target is defined as:
**Target = (Sum of array elements - x)**

```
public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            sum += nums[i];
        }
        int target = sum-x;

        int left = 0, right = 0;
        sum = 0;
        int len = 0;

		// This check is required in case we've to remove all the elements from array when target is 0.
		if(target == 0) return nums.length;

		// Sliding window 
        while(right < nums.length){
            sum += nums[right];
            while(sum > target && left <= right){
                sum -= nums[left];
                left++;
            }

            if(sum==target){
                len = Math.max(len, right - left + 1);
            }
            right++;
        }

		// If there is no Continuous subarray whose sum is equals to target, than return -1 
        if(len == 0) return -1;

		// len: Maximum window size which sums to target
		// nums.length - len => Min elements needed to remove from array
        return nums.length - len;
    }
```

