The first time I saw this problem, DP jumped into my mind and I spent 30min+ debugging big test cases. However it's a O(n^2) solution/aka 10^10 in this case and it got TLE. On the other hand, sliding window just takes O(n). **The problem can be translated into:  find the longest subarray with sum = sum(nums) - x**
```
    def minOperations(self, nums, x):
        n = len(nums)
        if x < nums[0] and x < nums[-1] or x > sum(nums):
            return -1
        i, res = 0, -1
        target = sum(nums) - x
        for j in range(n):
            target -= nums[j]
            if target == 0:
                res = max(res, j - i + 1)
            while target < 0:
                target += nums[i]
                i += 1
                if target == 0:
                    res = max(res, j - i + 1)
        if res != -1:
            return n - res
        else:
            return -1
