solutions.content:
We were asked to reduce X -> 0 by using only first and last element of array, and with each operation, our array was being updated. We can observe this question in the following way :
  1. Assume our array be like [a, b, ..........x, y, z] and assume that X can be reduced to 0 with [a,b,x,y,z], then we can say that a+b+x+y+z = X. Since we need to minimize the number of [a,b,x,y,z], we can do so by maximizing the remaining subarray. ie by maximizing the length of [c+d+.....v+w], we can minimize the length of [a,b,x,y,z]
  2. We also know that [a+b+c+d+.......w+x+y+z] (ie sum of array) is SUM. Thus we can say that sum of [c+d+......v+w] = SUM - X. 

  Now we have both, the array, and the sum of the subarray we need to maximize. Thus we can now apply the Longest Subarray Method to get the length of that subarray. Once we have that, we return Total_Length - SubArray_Length


```
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums, int x) {
        // We need to find Longest subarray with sum = total_sum - x
        // Using the prefix sum method to find the subarray size.
        vector <int> prefix;
        int temp_sum = 0;
        for(auto u : nums){
            temp_sum += u;
            prefix.push_back(temp_sum);
        }
        int sum = prefix.back();
        sum -= x;

        // If the sum of the subarray we need to find is zero, that simply means there is no subarray
        // because 1<=nums[i]<=10000
        if(sum == 0)
            return nums.size();

        // We store the prefix sum as key with its index as value
        map <int, int> mp;

        int len = -1;       // To store the length of Longest subarray
        /*
        Each time we encounter a subarray with sum 'k'(from index 0 to i) or a subarray with 
        sum 'prefix[i] - k'(from index of 'prefix[i]-k' to i), we compare it with current value 
        of len and update len accordingly.
        */
        for(int i = 0; i<prefix.size(); i++){
            if(prefix[i] == sum)
                len = i+1;
            if(mp.find(prefix[i]-sum) != mp.end()){
                int temp_len =  i+1 - mp[prefix[i]-sum];
                if(temp_len > len)
                    len = temp_len;
            }

            mp[prefix[i]] = i+1;
        }
        // If len remains -1, that means we did not find any subarray with subA_sum == sum
        if(len == -1)
            return -1;

        return nums.size() - len;
    }
};
```

