solutions.content:
This problem can be solved by both two pointers and binary search. There are only 3 ways in which we can reduce x to 0
1. Use elements only from left of array i.e., no elements from right
2. Use elements only from right of array i.e., no elements from left
3. Use few elements from left and few elements from right

**Two pointers:**
When we subtract x from sum of all elements in the array (**sum - x**), result is sum of all elements which we want to keep after reducing x to 0. If we can find a continuous subarray which gives us **sum - x**, then sum of all the remaining elements is x. So, it takes (length of array) -  (length of sub array with sum equals to **sum - x**)

```
 public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        int l = nums.length, ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i : nums){
            sum += i;
        }
        int k = sum - x;
        sum = 0;
        int jsum = 0;
        for(int i = 0, j = -1; i < l; i++){
            sum += nums[i];
            while(j < i && sum - jsum > k){
                jsum += nums[++j];
            }
            if(sum - jsum == k) ans = Math.min(ans, l - i + j);
        }
        return ans == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? -1 : ans;
    }
```

**Binary Search:**
Find the prefix sum of all elements and store in array. Now from right to left for each position **i**, find cumulative sum and use binary search to find the remaining sum i.e., **sum - cumsum** in the subarray  (0, i). At each position **i**, we can calcuate min of all
```
public int minOperations(int[] nums, int x) {
        int l = nums.length, ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int[] sum = new int[nums.length];
        sum[0] = nums[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < l; i++){
            sum[i] = sum[i - 1] + nums[i]; 
        }
        //is entire sum equals x, then one way is to use all elements
        int li = Arrays.binarySearch(sum, 0 , l , x);
        if(li >= 0) ans = Math.min(ans, li + 1);
        //from end to start, subtract sum from x and search for remaining in sum array
        for(int i = l - 1; i >= 0; i--){
            x -= nums[i];
            if(x == 0) {
                ans = Math.min(ans, l - i);
                break;
            }
            else if(x < 0) break;
            else{
                int index = Arrays.binarySearch(sum, 0, i, x);
                if(index < 0) continue;
                ans = Math.min(ans, l - i + index + 1);
            }
        }
        return ans == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? -1 : ans;
    }
```

