# Intuition
->1st observation is that sum <= 70 * 70 
->2nd obserbation is that to reduce space complexity (solution with dp have same complexity of O(5000*71)) we have to use something that can tell in linear time that if this sum is possible or not. so bitset<> is best for that 

# Approach
1. First row values mat[0][j] can be possible sums so will set the bit of possible sum on that index (eg. mat[0][0] = 4 so possible_sum = 00......00100)
2. iterate on each element of every row 
3. intialize bitset<>on_that_row = possibel_sum(bitset from previous row)
4. now left shift operation:  (prev << mat[i][j]). this will left shift the bitset<> previous row it same like addition of two number
(eg. bitst<>prev = 00......0010100 means upto previous row sum = 2 and sum = 4 are possibe now let mat[next_row][0] = 2 so will left shift two times the previous row bitset so on_that_row = 0000...01010000 means on this row possible sums = 4 and sum = 6) ,now for all sum will do OR operation
5. now again for each row update the possible_sum by on_that_row.
6. now just check set bit in  possible_sum and check for result.


If u have any doubt feel free to ask in comments section, hope u liked the solution.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n*m)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$ 

# Code
