For iterative dp, at each row we update all possible sum of values we can get. 
For example, if we at row r, we want to see what sum of values we have at row r-1,
and we can append mat numbers at row r to sum of values end at row r - 1 to form new
sum of values

dp[i] means if value i can be formed at current row
```class Solution {
    public int minimizeTheDifference(int[][] mat, int target) {
        int maxVal = 70 * mat.length;
        boolean[] dp = new boolean[maxVal + 1];
        dp[0] = true;
        for (int r = 0; r < mat.length; r++) {
            boolean[] dp2 = new boolean[maxVal + 1];
            for (int c = 0; c < mat[0].length; c++) {
                for (int val = mat[r][c]; val <= maxVal; val ++) {
                    dp2[val] = dp2[val] || dp[val - mat[r][c]];
                }
            }
            dp = dp2;
        }

        int res = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int val = 0; val <= maxVal; val++) {
            if (dp[val]) {
                res = Math.min(res, Math.abs(target - val));
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```


Second method is DFS with memo. Hight level idea of memo is always find and model depulication.
Deplicate here is: at a sepcific row, we have a same accumulative sum via different dfs path. So this 
different dfs path lead to a same condition. 
```
class Solution {
    public int minimizeTheDifference(int[][] mat, int target) {
        int[][] memo = new int[mat.length][4901];
        for (int[] arr : memo) {
            Arrays.fill(arr, -1);
        }
        return dfs(mat, 0, 0, target, memo);
    }

    private int dfs(int[][] mat, int index, int val, int target, int[][] memo) {
        if (index == mat.length) {
            return Math.abs(val - target);
        }
        if (memo[index][val] != -1) {
            return memo[index][val];
        }
        int res = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int c = 0; c < mat[0].length; c++) {
            res = Math.min(res, dfs(mat,index + 1, val + mat[index][c], target, memo));
        }
        memo[index][val] = res;
        return res;
    }
}
```

