solutions.content:
Bitset could be a good choic to this question:
1. the sums are in a relative small range (<5000);
2. use the index of the bitset to represent the possible sum;
3. use the bit shift operation to greatly reduce the time complexity. Only one shift operation can be equivalent to add a number to all the sums stored in the bitset.

More explanations can be found [https://algorithm-notes-allinone.blogspot.com/2021/08/leetcode-1981-minimize-difference.html](http://),


```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimizeTheDifference(vector<vector<int>>& mat, int target) {
        int m = mat.size(), n = mat.front().size(), cs = 5000, res = cs;
        bitset<5000> bt;
        for(int i=0; i<n; ++i) bt[mat[0][i]] = 1;
        for(int i=1; i<m; ++i) {
            bitset<5000> pre = bt, nxt;
            for(int j=0; j<n; ++j) {
                nxt |= pre << mat[i][j];
            }
            bt = nxt;
        }
        for(int i=0; i<cs; ++i) {
            if(bt[i]) res = min(res, abs(i-target));
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

