solutions.content:
* Actually, we need to find a range of sum on which we can apply DP.
* So find the sum of smallest element(let say s) from each row. If this sum is greater than or equal to the target`(s>=target)`, then no other better solution exists and `abs(target-s)` will be our answer.
	For eg. Let the sum we got from smaller elements is 450 and target is 400. All the other sum in the matrix will be greater than 450 and hence the absolute difference will increase.
* If s < target, then we have to find a range on which we can apply DP. The `lower bound of this range will definitely be s`. `The upper bound will be target + abs(target-s)`. Above this, we will not be getting a better answer.
* So the last step is to run a loop on this range and we will find that the particular sum exist or not in the matrix using DP.

```
class Solution {
    int dp[71][3001];
	// DP to find a particular sum exist or not 
    bool helper(int sum,int m,int n,vector<vector<int>>& mat){
        if(m==0 && sum==0){
            return true;
        }
        if(m==0 || sum<0){
            return false;
        }
        if(dp[m][sum]!=-1){
            return dp[m][sum];
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(mat[m-1][i]>sum) continue;
            bool check = helper(sum-mat[m-1][i],m-1,n,mat);
            if(check){
                return dp[m][sum]=true;    
            } 
        }
        return dp[m][sum]=false;
    }

public:
    int minimizeTheDifference(vector<vector<int>>& mat, int target) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof dp);
        int ans=INT_MAX;
        int s=0,m =mat.size(),n=mat[0].size();
		// Finding sum of smallest element from each row
        for(int i =0;i<m;i++){
            int y=INT_MAX;
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                y=min(y,mat[i][j]);
            }
            s+=y;
        }
        if(s>=target){
            return abs(s-target);
        }
        int x = abs(s-target); // Upper limit
		// Running loop over the range
        for(int i=s;i<target+x;i++){
            if(helper(i,m,n,mat)){
                ans=min(ans,abs(target-i));
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
